                            <comment id="13032255" author="esammer" created="Thu, 12 May 2011 05:04:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a hard time seeing how this ever worked. Per the patch on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-954&quot; title=&quot;The new interface&amp;#39;s Context objects should be interfaces&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAPREDUCE-954&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAPREDUCE-954&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I backed out the changes but the original code for MockMapContext has this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; MockMapContext(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; List&amp;lt;Pair&amp;lt;KEYIN, VALUEIN&amp;gt;&amp;gt; in, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Counters counters)
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException, InterruptedException {

      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Configuration(),
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; TaskAttemptID(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;mrunit-jt&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, 0, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;, 0, 0),
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; MockOutputCommitter(), &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; MockReporter(counters), &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;);
    ...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To me, it seems like you get a new Configuration object no matter what in the Context object which means the configuration passed in by the user (via MapDriver#withConfiguration()) simply never gets used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Aaron, thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13032264" author="gwu" created="Thu, 12 May 2011 06:17:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had noticed a related problem where the Configuration was not passed to the MockOutputCollector when I was trying to give it a Configuration with AvroSerialization added.  Here&apos;s the patch I used to fix it for that case &amp;#8211; I hadn&apos;t noticed that it was also broken for the MockMapContext and possibly others.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13039994" author="esammer" created="Thu, 26 May 2011 23:48:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using initial patch from Garret, found the last few remaining instances where configuration wasn&apos;t passed along and fixed. This may have worked but been broken due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-954&quot; title=&quot;The new interface&amp;#39;s Context objects should be interfaces&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAPREDUCE-954&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAPREDUCE-954&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; not being the final patch or something equally hinky.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests pass. Pushed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
